p width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/unonecn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>none CN</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/21/01 8:03:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> druid, enchanter, paladin</span><hr size=1> The classic set of healer, tank and caster will take a three person group a long way in PvE and PvP.  <br>
<br>
Druids are the best choice for a small group since they can cover many needs (SoW, healing, teleportation, snare) and many wants (damage shield, tracking, regeneration, resists).  Clerics are a powerful class, but their strength shows in large encounters and larger groups.  Complete heal should not be necessary in the ideal small group experience.  Shamans share many of the same spells as druids and a pet would aid dealing damage, but the need for teleports (and limited PvE abilities of the wizard) makes druid the choice.<br>
<br>
Enchanters reduce downtime.  They also turn bad situations into good ones.  Mana regeneration, melee haste, crowd control, debuffs and pets (potentially the best pets in the game).  Magicians are too limited.  As are wizards.  A bard might be able to fill the role of the enchanter, but even the best bard would be hard pressed to maintain all buffs while controlling a bad pull.<br>
<br>
Paladins are underrated tanks.  With stuns and FoL and heals even warriors would be hard pressed to outtaunt the paladin and taunt will be important for this small group in many XP situations.  A secondary healer is always of benefit, especially in PvP.  Lay of Hands is the ultimate Get Out of Jail Free card.  Other melee classes might deal more damage, but the defensive abilities the paladin can bring the small group, especially in PvP, are worth the sacrifice. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=FAEBD7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/uvachir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vachir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tavern Regular</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/21/01 9:55:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: druid, enchanter, paladin</span><hr size=1> druid/enchanter/paladin actually sounds pretty good, you would get ports, sow, track, mez, clarity, res and LoH.  This group would probably be maximum versatility at the cost of power where a group like warrior/cleric/wizard would be high power at the cost of versatility. <p>--------------------<BR>
